The paper presents experiments on semantic segmentation using a convolutional architecture, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a modified DenseNet-169 model suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.LG), and the limited computing resources used for training may indicate a focus on efficient algorithms (cs.AI). The evaluation of the model on multiple benchmark datasets suggests a focus on generalization and robustness (cs.NE), and the fact that the experiments are performed in concordance with the guidelines of the Robust Vision Challenge ROB 2018 suggests a focus on robotics and perception (cs.RO).
